r head) (feat. beabadoobee)\" on Spotify}}</ref> (stylized in [[Letter case#All lowercase|all lowercase]]) is a song by Canadian rapper [[Powfu]], featuring Filipino-British singer-songwriter [[Beabadoobee]]. Following Powfu signing to [[Columbia Records]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/powfu-breaks-down-the-meaning-of-death-bed|title=Powfu Breaks Down The Meaning Of \"Death Bed\"|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Reneau|first=Steven|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref> the song was released on streaming services on February 8, 2020, after initially being uploaded to [[SoundCloud]] in 2019. The song samples 2017 song \"Coffee\" by Beabadoobee, whom is also credited as a feature.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/08/powfu-beabadoobees-death-bed-picks-up-pop-radio-airplay-reaches-50-million-spotify-streams/|title=Powfu & Beabadoobee's \"Death Bed\" Picks Up Pop Radio Airplay, Reaches 50 Million Spotify Streams|website=Headline Planet|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=March 8, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe song went viral on the video sharing app [[TikTok]] in early 2020.<ref name=\"Genius BG\">{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/powfu-s-death-bed-samples-beabadoobee-s-coffee|title=Powfu's Viral Hit \"Death Bed\" Arrives On Streaming Services After Lengthy Sample Clearance Delay|website=Genius|last=Fu|first=Eddie|date=February 13, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe song's commercial release was delayed by a year due to the clearance of the [[Sampling (music)|sample]] of Beabadoobee's 2017 song \"Coffee\". Powfu said on [[Twitter]] in April 2019 that he had not put it on [[Spotify]] because he was \"scared [he'd] get in trouble from the sample [he] use[s] in it\", but said he \"would upload it anyway\" and told his followers to give him \"a week and a half\". It was finally released to streaming and download services in February 2020.<ref name=\"Genius BG\"/>\n\n==Composition