{"title_page": "Sietland", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}\n{{Infobox German location\n|Art               = Samtgemeinde\n|Name              = Sietland\n|year              = 1970\n|dissolved         = 2010-12-31\n|Wappen            = Wappen-Sietland.png\n|coordinates       = {{coord|53|44|N|8|55|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|Lageplan          = Samtgemeinde Sietland in CUX.svg\n|Bundesland        = Niedersachsen\n|Landkreis         = Cuxhaven\n|Fl\u00e4che            = 143.79\n|Einwohner         = 5449\n|Stand             = 2009-12-31\n|Gliederung        = 4\n|Website           = [https://web.archive.org/web/20070927011646/http://www.sietland.de/ www.sietland.de]\n}}\n'''Sietland''' is a former ''[[Samtgemeinde]]'' (\"collective municipality\") in the [[Cuxhaven (district)|district of Cuxhaven]], in [[Lower Saxony]], [[Germany]]. It was situated in the historical [[Land of Hadeln]] approx. 20&nbsp;km southeast of [[Cuxhaven]]. Its seat was in the village Ihlienworth. On 1 January 2011 it merged with the ''Samtgemeinde'' [[Hadeln]] to form the new ''Samtgemeinde'' [[Land Hadeln (Samtgemeinde)|Land Hadeln]].\n\nThe ''Samtgemeinde'' Sietland consisted of the following municipalities:\n\n# [[Ihlienworth]]\n# [[Odisheim]] \n# [[Steinau, Lower Saxony|Steinau]] \n# [[Wanna, Germany|Wanna]] \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Cuxhaven (district)]]\n[[Category:Former Samtgemeinden in Lower Saxony]]\n\n{{Cuxhaven-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}\n{{Infobox German location\n|Art               = Samtgemeinde\n|Name              = Sietland\n|Gegr\u00fcndet         = 1970\n|dissolved = 2010-12-31\n|Wappen            = Wappen-Sietland.png\n|coordinates       = {{coord|53|44|N|8|55|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|Lageplan          = Samtgemeinde Sietland in CUX.svg\n|Bundesland        = Niedersachsen\n|Landkreis         = Cuxhaven\n|Fl\u00e4che            = 143.79\n|Einwohner         = 5449\n|Stand             = 2009-12-31\n|Gliederung        = 4\n|Adresse           = Hauptstra\u00dfe 40<br />21775 Ihlienworth\n|Website           = [https://web.archive.org/web/20070927011646/http://www.sietland.de/ www.sietland.de]\n|B\u00fcrgermeister     = Maik Schwanemann\n|Partei            =  \n}}\n'''Sietland''' is a former ''[[Samtgemeinde]]'' (\"collective municipality\") in the [[Cuxhaven (district)|district of Cuxhaven]], in [[Lower Saxony]], [[Germany]]. It was situated in the historical [[Land of Hadeln]] approx. 20&nbsp;km southeast of [[Cuxhaven]]. Its seat was in the village Ihlienworth. On 1 January 2011 it merged with the ''Samtgemeinde'' [[Hadeln]] to form the new ''Samtgemeinde'' [[Land Hadeln (Samtgemeinde)|Land Hadeln]].\n\nThe ''Samtgemeinde'' Sietland consisted of the following municipalities:\n\n# [[Ihlienworth]]\n# [[Odisheim]] \n# [[Steinau, Lower Saxony|Steinau]] \n# [[Wanna, Germany|Wanna]] \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Cuxhaven (district)]]\n[[Category:Former Samtgemeinden in Lower Saxony]]\n\n{{Cuxhaven-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sietland"}
